  <sect1 id="prereq">
    <title>Build Prerequisites</title>

    <para>
      &YP; was designed to have only few library dependencies, and to
      build on most popular Unixes.
    </para>

      <para>&YP; depends on two libraries</para>

      <para>
	<itemizedlist>
	  <listitem>
	    <simpara>OpenSSL (<ulink
	    url="http://www.openssl.org">http://www.openssl.org</ulink>)</simpara></listitem>
	  <listitem>
	    <simpara>curses or ncurses (<ulink
		url="http://www.gnu.org/software/ncurses/">http://www.gnu.org/software/ncurses/</ulink>)</simpara>
	  </listitem>
	</itemizedlist>
      </para>

      <para>
	As of version 0.3 &YP; uses GNU Gettext for
	internationalization, hence GNU Gettext is an optional
	dependency.
      </para>

    <sect2 id="supportedplatforms">
      <title>Supported Platforms</title>

      &supplatforms;
    </sect2>

    <sect2 id="compilers">
      <title>Supported Compilers</title>

      <para>&YP; is written in C++, so you obviously need a C++
	compiler to compile. It compiles out of the box using the
	following compilers</para>

      <para>
	<itemizedlist>
	  <listitem>
	    <simpara>Sun/Solaris Studio 12.2 C++ Compiler or later</simpara>
	  </listitem>
	  <listitem>
	    <simpara>GNU GCC</simpara>
	  </listitem>
	</itemizedlist>
      </para>
    </sect2>

  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="buildinstr">
    <title>Brief Build Instructions</title>

    <para>
      &YP; uses a <command>configure</command> script as generated by
      <command>autoconf</command> and friends for configuring the
      build process of &YP;. Change to the directory where you
      unpacked <filename>&YPPKG;</filename> and simply type
    </para>

    <para>
<screen>
  <prompt>#</prompt> <literal>./configure</literal>
</screen>
    </para>

    <para>
      on the command line. The <command>configure</command> script
      will then check the system and prepare for the build process.
    </para>

    <para>
      If the <command>configure</command> script successfully
      finishes, type
    </para>

    <para>
<screen>
  <prompt>#</prompt> <literal>make</literal>
</screen>
    </para>

    <para>
      &YP; will now be built. After the build has finished, switch to
      the root user if not done already, and type
    </para>

    <para>
<screen>
  <prompt>#</prompt> <literal>make install</literal>
</screen>
    </para>

    <para>
      This will install &YP; into the
      <filename>/usr/local/bin</filename> directory, if the prefix has
      not been changed by providing
      <option>--prefix=<replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable></option>
      to the <command>configure</command> script.
    </para>

    <para>
      To start &YP; issue <filename>/usr/local/bin</filename>/&yp; on
      the command line.
    </para>
  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="confoptions">
    <title>Brief configure Options Description</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>--prefix=</option><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>
	</term>

	<listitem>
	  <para><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable> is the base directory
	    where &YP; will be installed. The executable is installed
	    in
	    <replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable><filename>/bin</filename>.
	  </para>
	</listitem>

      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>--with-openssl=</option><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>
	</term>

	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Installation prefix of OpenSSL. The build system will
	    search for OpenSSL headers in
	    <filename><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>/include</filename>
	    and for OpenSSL libraries in
	    <filename><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>/lib</filename>.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>--disable-csv2yapet</option>
	</term>

	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    If given the <command>csv2yapet</command> import utility
	    will not be built.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>--disable-nls</option>
	</term>

	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Disables Native Language Support.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

    </variablelist>
  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="wgi">
    <title>What gets installed?</title>

    <para>
      Upon issuing <command>make <option>install</option></command>
      the following files are installed in
      <replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>
   </para>

    <variablelist>

      <varlistentry>
	<term><filename><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>/bin/yapet</filename></term>
	<listitem><para>The &YP; binary.</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term><filename><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>/bin/[csv2yapet|yapet2csv]</filename></term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Utility for converting CSV files into &YP; files.
	  </para>

	  <para>
	    <filename>csv2yapet</filename> and
	    <filename>yapet2csv</filename> will be installed only when
	    the build of <command>csv2yapet</command> has not been
	    disabled.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term><filename><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>/share/man/man1/[yapet.1|csv2yapet.1|yapet2csv.1|yapet_config.5|yapet_colors.5]</filename></term>

	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    The manual page for &YP;.
	  </para>

	  <para>
	    <filename>csv2yapet.1</filename> and
	    <filename>yapet2csv.1</filename> will be installed only
	    when the build of <command>csv2yapet</command> has not
	    been disabled.
	  </para>

	  <para>
	    Files won't be installed when installation of
	    documentation files has been disabled.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term><filename><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>/share/applications/yapet.desktop</filename></term>

	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    The desktop file for GNOME et al.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term><filename><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>/share/doc/[AUTHORS|COPYING|DESIGN|LICENSE|README]</filename></term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Various documentation files.
	  </para>

	  <para>
	    Files won't be installed when installation of
	    documentation files has been disabled using
	    <option>--disable-install-doc</option>.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term><filename><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>/share/doc/html/[DESIGN.html|README.html|yapet.html|csv2yapet.html]</filename></term>

	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Various documentation files in HTML format.
	  </para>

	  <para>
	    <filename>csv2yapet.html</filename> will be installed only when
	    the build of <command>csv2yapet</command> has not been
	    disabled.
	  </para>

	  <para>
	    Files won't be installed when installation of
	    documentation files has been disabled using
	    <option>--disable-install-doc</option>.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term><filename><replaceable>&lt;PATH&gt;</replaceable>/share/locale/<replaceable>LANG</replaceable></filename></term>

	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    The translation files.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

    </variablelist>

  </sect1>

